    Garam Masala (blend)
    Sumac
    Zaâ€™atar
    Nigella Seeds
    Asafoetida

Asian
    Five-Spice Powder
    Sichuan Peppercorns
    Galangal (dried)
    Dried Ginger

Latin American
    Annatto Seeds
    Mexican Oregano
    Chipotle Powder

African
    Berbere
    Grains of Paradise

===================================================================
CHEF TIPS 
===================================================================

whole vs ground: 
    Whole spices retain flavor longer
    Toast before grinding

storage: 
    airtight containers
    cool/dark place 
    avoid heat and moisture

pairing: 
    balance heat with sweetmess (i.e. cinnamon + chili)
    balance acidity with earthy spices

- taste as you go. spices evolve during cooking 
- experiment in small batches. spice mistakes are hard to fix 
- built a mental map of spice families and their cultural contexts

===================================================================
CULTURAL SPICE LOGIC 
===================================================================

indian                  layered complexity; whole spices bloomed in fat, ground spices later 
middle eastern          warn blends (cinnamon, allspice) with bright notes (sumac) 
asian                   balance of heat, sweet, and umami (ginger, star anise, sichuan pepper) 
latin american          chili-forward with earthy cumin and oregano 
